    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Sensitivity analysis: material modulus and contact friction on F1717 QoIs",
    "description": "A one-at-a-time sensitivity study varied titanium elastic modulus ±5% (110–121 GPa) and screw-rod interface friction coefficient 0.1–0.4. Construct stiffness varied by less than 3.2% across the modulus range, while yield force exhibited a 6.1% range with friction as the dominant driver, confirming that contact representation is the highest-priority uncertainty source for this COU."
  },
